Description:
Contract is for 3 months, with a potential to increase to 6 months.
Tectah is a US, UK and Ireland based card payments and technology software provider to SME’s.
We provide our customers with the solutions they need to make their business a success. These solutions include POS Software and Systems, mobile apps for ordering and web apps for engaging with consumers either through loyalty or reservations. By linking these solutions to the Tectah EPoS (till) system, we help hospitality brands to understand their customers’ behaviour and preferences, enabling them to excel in an increasingly competitive market.
What you'll do
You will be responsible for creating and implementing the POS Software for the F&B and Grocery Market. You will help to modernise the hospitality industry by working on the latest features and improvements for these applications. You will feel a sense of pride when you see the work you do having a direct positive impact in this industry.
Your day will be split between writing new features, improving existing code, code reviews, and story estimation. We believe in making things better and are always open to new ideas that can help the team work better.
Working within an agile delivery team, you will participate in all aspects of delivering software projects. You will participate in the technical design, development, and maintenance of our environments. You will ensure quality by writing unit tests and performing code reviews.
Who you are
You will enjoy a fast-paced development environment and writing good quality code is important to you. You will have had experience writing complex applications in at least one OO programming language but you will enjoy learning new technologies and be happy to sometimes work on code written in a language you haven’t used before.
You will have experience with Web development and be at home writing SQL queries and building websites to life from designs. You will have time to help out your colleagues and not be afraid to ask them for help sometimes. You will be keen to bring suggestions for improvements to ensure the team continues to produce industry-leading tools and technologies.
You MUST be able to demonstrate strong experience in the following areas:

Proven industry experience with customer facing or internal facing web applications
3+ years minimum experience in writing applications in one or more of the following:
C#, .NET Core, .NET 6, .NET Framework,
PHP, Symfony, Laravel, Wordpress
JS/React
HTML/CSS, Wordpress design
Experience with Microsoft SQL/MySQL, including stored procedures, indexes, triggers, and functions
Experience in a varied range of integration and API architectural styles (REST, SOA, microservices, message bus, API gateways/proxies)
Experience writing unit tests
Knowledge of Computer Science fundamentals
Ability to translate business goals into technology solutions
Strong communication skills, with the ability to reduce complex problems and communicate at all levels
Able to work as part of a multi-disciplinary team but also being known as a self-starter with a proactive approach

You will have an interest in and may be able to demonstrate experience in:

Good understanding and practical knowledge of the full software development lifecycle; design patterns; architecture patterns; SOLID principles; Cloud technology; API maintenance; CI/CD and DevSecOps.
Experience in app development
Deploying Docker containers and Kubernetes
Cloud platforms such as AWS, Azure, GCP
TDD and BDD

What we require:
Access to a computer with strong internet connection
UK Shift Pattern, we ask our staff to work 9am – 5pm GMT.
What we value
Passion, Teamwork, Innovation and Professionalism are the values we believe make us the company we are. We’re looking for someone who understands great culture and will help us shape it as it evolves.

On-Site
At Eon, our mission is to make patients healthier and healthcare affordable. Eon Patient Management, or EPM as we like to call it, identifies patients with disease risk and streamlines clinical decision analysis so clinicians can work at the top of their licenses. With unique solutions across multiple disease states, we drive unprecedented adherence to care pathways, so that more patients are seen and more survive. When patients win, healthcare systems win - both clinically and financially.
As a market leader in incidental tracking and patient management, Eon is pioneering the use of Artificial Intelligence to enable healthcare enterprises, ranging from small health systems to large, national-scale IDN’s. We have a unique and dynamic team that is focused on results, and employment opportunities both local to our Denver and Pakistan offices, Canada, and remote based.
The Opportunity
Eon is looking for a DevOps Engineer that wants to make a difference in healthcare.
As a DevOps Engineer you will:

Design Multi-cloud infrastructure (AWS and Azure) that is secure, scalable, developer-friendly, and highly available.
Handle the full DevOps toolchain and be the go-to person for developers.
Administer and troubleshoot Linux/Windows based systems.
Build and maintain operational tools for deployment, monitoring, and analysis of AWS infrastructure and systems.
Responsible for monitoring, logging, alerting, tracing, security, CI/CD, and core automation services.
Design and implement novel solutions to automate cloud-environment provisioning
Automate and improve development and release processes
Ensure that systems are safe and secure against cybersecurity threats

Skills and Requirements:

Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering or IT
At least 3 years of experience building and maintaining AWS or Azure infrastructure.
Solid experience in a python development role to develop utility functions, DevOps focused.
Solid experience with Containerization | Experience building docker images and running and troubleshooting docker containers.
Must have experience with AWS ECS and EKS
Must have Infrastructure Automation experience with Terraform / Cloud Formation.
Experience in the design, maintenance and management of ELK stacks.
Strong scripting skills (ability to write Bash script, Python etc.)
Strong experience with python, Node.js cloud SDKs i.e. boto3 for using AWS services API.
Solid understanding of fundamental technologies like DNS, Load Balancing, SSL, networking, and security best practices.
Familiarity with Cybersecurity compliance standards such as SOC2, HIPAA, CIS Benchmarks
Familiarity with common web services, technologies, architectures, and related practices to make them reliable

We pride ourselves for being a culture-based company buzzing with high-energy. Aside from the enthusiastic environment, you'll enjoy:

Provident Fund

Health insurance

Generous vacation time

Work from home days

Awesome team members

Description:
As an SEO specialist, you'll identify strategies, techniques and tactics to increase the number of visitors to a website and obtain a high-ranking placement in the results page of search engines. By generating more leads for the business you'll open up new opportunities for driving growth and profit.
Responsibilities:

A functional understanding of HTML and CSS.
Develop optimization strategies that increase the company's website search engine results rankings.
Execute tests, collect and analyze data and results, identify trends and insights in order to achieve maximum ROI.
Manage the expenses of SEO campaigns, staying on budget, estimating monthly costs and reconciling differences.
Research and implement search engine optimization recommendations
Create and execute link building strategy.
Determine measurable goals that demonstrate improvement in marketing efforts.
Write compelling and high-quality website content, including blog posts and page descriptions to improve website search results.
Make technical recommendations to developers
Constantly check search terms, rankings and analytics to monitor performance of client websites and make recommendations for improvement.
Drive targeted and loyal traffic to a website by community building.
Use social media to distribute content and encourage more external sites to link to your content - giving you more authority

Day-to-Day Duties:

Conduct page optimization for search engine marketing.
Monitor daily performance metrics with SEO tools such as Google analytics to understand SEO strategy performance.
Collaborate with others within the marketing department to manage SEO strategy.
Perform ongoing keyword research, discovery and optimization for new SEO keywords to use throughout the company website and marketing materials.
Closely collaborate with the web development team to ensure SEO best practices are properly followed throughout website content.
Change website architecture, content, linking and other factors to improve SEO positions for target keywords.

Requirements:

Experience with Google and Bing’s services, including Analytics and Webmaster Tools.
Experience with Google’s Keyword Tool.
Experience in building inbound organic search traffic and improving SERPs.
The ability to work with back-end SEO elements such as .htaccess, robots.txt, metadata, site speed optimization, and related skills.
Proven success in link building and viral strategies.
The ability to deploy an effective local and long-tail search strategy.
A deep understanding of mobile strategy and how it relates to SEO.
A solid grasp of how blogging, press releases, social media, and related strategies go hand-in-hand with SEO.
A background in creating reports showing web analytics data and site evaluations.
An up-to-date, working knowledge of current, past, and projected trends in the SEO industry.

Please note this is a full-time office-based job for our Lahore office.

We are looking for a CodeIgniter/Laravel Developer responsible for managing back-end services and the interchange of data between the server and the users. Your primary focus will be the development of all server-side logic, definition, and maintenance of the central database, and ensuring high performance and responsiveness to requests from the front end. You will also be responsible for integrating the front-end elements built by your co-workers into the application. Therefore, a basic understanding of front-end technologies is necessary as well. PHP Developer responsibilities:
✔ The candidate must be proficient in MVC frameworks such as CodeIgniter, Laravel, or CakePHP.
✔ The candidate must have hands-on experience with JavaScript including AJAX, JSON, JQuery, and other Javascript frameworks like Vue, ReactJS, AngularJS, and NodeJS.
✔ He/She must have sound knowledge of MySQL or MongoDB.
✔ The candidate should have experience about 3rd party API implementation, and payment implementation including PayPal, Stripe, 2Checkout, Merchant Account, etc.
✔ Candidates who haven’t hands-on experience in PHP frameworks or WordPress, Joomla, Drupal, ZendOpenCart Platforms, then PLEASE DO NOT APPLY as we do not want custom PHP or fresh coders.
✔ Integration of user-facing elements developed by front-end developers.
✔ Build efficient testable and reusable PHP modules.✔ Solve complex performance problems and architectural challenges.
✔ Integration of data storage solutions will be a plus point.
Laravel developer requirements:
✔ Bachelor’s degree in computer science, software engineering, or a similar field.
✔ Previous experience working as a PHP developer.
✔ Strong knowledge of PHP web frameworks such as Laravel, and Yii.
✔ Understanding the fully synchronous behavior of PHP.
✔ Basic understanding of front-end technologies such as JavaScript, HTML5, and CSS3.
✔ Familiarity with SQL/NoSQL databases and their declarative query languages.
Experience Required: 2-3years of experience should be requiredIndustryComputer Software
Employment TypeFull-time
Job Type: Full-time

Your primary focus will be the development of all server-side logic, definition, and maintenance of the central database, and ensuring high performance and responsiveness to requests from the front end. You will also be responsible for integrating the front-end elements built by your co-workers into the application. Therefore, a basic understanding of front-end technologies is necessary as well. PHP Developer responsibilities:
✔ The candidate must be proficient in MVC frameworks such as CodeIgniter, Laravel, or CakePHP.
✔ The candidate must have hands-on experience with JavaScript including AJAX, JSON, JQuery, and other Javascript frameworks like Vue, ReactJS, AngularJS, and NodeJS.
✔ He/She must have sound knowledge of MySQL or MongoDB.
✔ The candidate should have experience about 3rd party API implementation, and payment implementation including PayPal, Stripe, 2Checkout, Merchant Account, etc.
✔ Candidates who haven’t hands-on experience in PHP frameworks or WordPress, Joomla, Drupal, ZendOpenCart Platforms, then PLEASE DO NOT APPLY as we do not want custom PHP or fresh coders.
✔ Integration of user-facing elements developed by front-end developers.
✔ Build efficient testable and reusable PHP modules.✔ Solve complex performance problems and architectural challenges.
✔ Integration of data storage solutions will be a plus point.
Laravel developer requirements:
✔ Bachelor’s degree in computer science, software engineering, or a similar field.
✔ Previous experience working as a PHP developer.
✔ Strong knowledge of PHP web frameworks such as Laravel, and Yii.
✔ Understanding the fully synchronous behavior of PHP.
✔ Basic understanding of front-end technologies such as JavaScript, HTML5, and CSS3.
✔ Familiarity with SQL/NoSQL databases and their declarative query languages.

Job description
Preesoft is looking for a full-stack web developer who will participate in developing new and existing Web applications and growing amounts of Laravel sites. We’re looking for someone who is confident in their own skills while constantly seeking to learn and keep up with modern practices. Knowledge and appreciation for the art of journalism are required.
Our two main technologies that we are investing most of our resources in are Laravel (a modern PHP framework), which we use for our API, and Vue.js (JavaScript frontend framework), which currently powers the fronted application. We are looking for a candidate who is already interested and excited by the Laravel ecosystem and writing code that adheres to SOLID principles.
Key Responsibilities:
· Add features to existing Website/Portal
· Create new websites/ Portal
· Manage code in version control
· Program complex features involving multiple technologies integrated into websites
· Write quality OOP code and follow existing development standards
· Implement design spec layouts using Vue/Tailwind components and VueX
· Write unit tests for your own code
· Work with the rest of the team to discuss best approaches for projects in the pipeline
· Be involved in discussing projects' business objectives and how the team should schedule a project's releases to best meet them.
Required Skills:
· 2+ years of experience
· object-oriented design and implementation experience, data structures, algorithm design and problem solving
· PHP knowledge and experience is required (Laravel strongly preferred)
· Knowledge of Vue.js and VueX & React Js or similar JavaScript frontend framework is required
· Experience working with 3rd party APIs
· MySQL knowledge required, Redis or MongoDB a plus
· Experience writing automated tests is a huge plus
· JavaScript
· VueJs
· Git
· Server and database management
· Experience in general web development (academic and professional)
· Understanding of networking and internet mechanics
· Maturity, judgment, negotiation/influence skills, analytical skills and leadership skills
· Deals well with ambiguous/undefined problems; ability to think abstractly
· Ability to synthesize requirements underlying feature request, recommend alternative technical and business approaches, and facilitate engineering efforts to meet aggressive timelines
Ideal Skills:
· Modern tooling (PHP: Composer, JavaScript: web pack, gulp, babel, Payment Gateways, Twilio API Integration etc)
· VueJS
· React Js
· Laravel
· VueX
· Knowledge and Critical Skills*
. Ability to manage multiple tasks simultaneously, problem-solve and work as part of a team
· Exceptional verbal, written and email communication skills
· Ability to proactively react to changes and improvement opportunities
· Project management skills and understanding how to manage priorities of multiple stakeholders in a complex environment
· Strong time management skills
· Strong work ethic and willingness to go over and above
Opportunities:
Work directly with leadership in the growing web development department within an expanding creative communications and marketing company
· Exposure to creative opportunities for applying programming skills to real-world applications and processes
· Fast-paced environment with optimal opportunity for growth

 Provide technical solutions as and when required support, re-factor and enhance an existing production system. 

 Review, analyze requirements and develop estimates / task lists based on those requirements.

Location : Lahore/Islamabad 


Requirements:
 A minimum of 2 year experience in HTML, HTML5, Javascript, JQuery 

 Ability to work in an agile development environment 

 Knowledge of best practices for the full software development life cycle, including coding standards, code reviews, source control management and testing. 

 Strong problem solving and debugging skills. 

 Good verbal and written communication skills for client interaction. 

 Excellent organizational skills, including the ability to work under pressure in a fast paced environment across multiple small and large scale projects. 


Essential Skills:
 HTML5 

 XHTML 

 CSS/CSS3 

 JavaScript/Coffee Script 

 JQuery 

 AngularJS 

 Git/SVN 

 Photoshop (Not as designer but for basic stuff) 

 Responsive designs/implementations 

 Experience of at least one version control systems (SVN/Git) 


Nice to have:
 Express/NodeJS 

 Sencha Touch/ExtJS 

 MongoDB 


CSS framework, Like: Less or SASS 

 Bootstrap or similar 

 Linux environment 

 Amazon Cloud Front/S3 SDK 

 Modernizr 

 Underscore 

 RESTful web services, AJAX
